25/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Chief of Staff Metodi Stamboliski met with Albanian Chief of Staff PÃ«llumb Qazimi on Thursday (24 April).
Their focus was military co-operation, specifically in light of both countries' aspirations to join NATO.
The three officials also discussed the idea of establishing joint border patrols to fight illegal trafficking.
In other news, the newspaper <I>Dnevnik</I> reported details Friday of a new national strategy for security and defence.
The document envisions establishment of a Centre for Crisis Management, co-ordinating efforts of all state institutions working to stabilise the country and prepare for NATO membership.
(Dnevnik - 25/04/03;
MIA - 24/04/03)
